{
  "stem": "2713.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The first-- the first bomb fell in Wadowice on this-- on our restaurant.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 90,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And three people were killed there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, when I came back to my father, after-- after a while, then it took about another couple weeks or three weeks, and then mail started to-- to arrive.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were very happy, because then even we could send them parcels.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were quite happy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were only hoping that the war won't last too long, and we'd be able to go back to our home.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Unfortunately, it didn't happen so.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then they were trying-- you see, Wadowice belonged once to Germany in the First World War.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were trying to-- the Germans wanted to make a border there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when we heard this, we wanted mum and-- and her-- the sisters to leave there, to come to Dzialoszyce.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we didn't realize that the border, they will make it so fast.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Unfortunately, the did it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and they was-- they were staying there, for a while, because we had to make arrangements, how to bring them to Dzialoszyce.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was somebody in-- in Wadowice that would take us through the border, for a lot of money, which we did.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And after a while, they managed to cross the border, all of them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they were very lucky, because there were no Jews, anymore, in the city anywhere.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Jews were-- the Jews were in ghettos or they were in the concentration camps or whatever.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not from our family.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not from our-- but why I'm saying about the ghetto, because, when-- when my sister and-- and my mother went to Cracow, well, to start with, they had to wear a-- a yellow-- a star of David.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
